## Accessibility Checklist for Components

Before marking a component as done, verify:

- [ ] Interactive elements use semantic HTML (`<button>`, `<a>`, `<input>`) not `<div onClick>`
- [ ] If a non-semantic element must be interactive, it has `role`, `tabIndex`, and keyboard handler
- [ ] Icons without adjacent text have `aria-label` or `aria-hidden="true"`
- [ ] Error messages are associated with their input via `aria-describedby`
- [ ] Focus styles are visible (do not use `outline-none` without a custom replacement)
- [ ] Colour is not the only indicator of state (also use text, icon, or shape)
- [ ] Dynamic content changes are announced with `aria-live` where appropriate

---

## What NOT to Do

- Do not use `any` in props interfaces - use `unknown` and narrow the type
- Do not read directly from `localStorage` in a component - use a hook or store
- Do not `console.log` in production components - use a logger utility
- Do not put business logic in UI components
- Do not create a new `fetch` call inside a component - use a service function
- Do not use inline styles (`style={% raw %}{{ ... }}{% endraw %}`) - use {{ styling }} classes
- Do not skip error and loading states - they are part of the DoD
